.TH "intel_edp_drrs_invalidate" 9 "intel_edp_drrs_invalidate" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
intel_edp_drrs_invalidate \- Disable Idleness DRRS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" intel_edp_drrs_invalidate
.BI "(struct drm_i915_private *dev_priv "  ","
.BI "unsigned int frontbuffer_bits "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
i915 device
.IP "frontbuffer_bits" 12
frontbuffer plane tracking bits
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function gets called everytime rendering on the given planes start.
Hence DRRS needs to be Upclocked, i.e. (LOW_RR -> HIGH_RR).

Dirty frontbuffers relevant to DRRS are tracked in busy_frontbuffer_bits.
